fields.Dialogue Text: "Or even better," he stops to correct himself, "just leave it be."

Half Light: "This flimsy magazine is right. Deep..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This flimsy magazine is right. Deep down you know the only *true* stakes are life and glory, or death by fiery dismemberment.

fields.Title: La Fumée, Vol. 1 No. 4: "Unsurprisingly, much of this sectio..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Unsurprisingly, much of this section is taken up with articles declaring unqualified support for the dockworkers' strike.

fields.Title: You: "Why should I care? This doesn't hav..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Why should I care? This doesn't have anything to do with me.

fields.Title: La Fumée, Vol. 1 No. 4: "The front of this quarterly journal..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The front of this quarterly journal features a large, satirical portrait of the late King Frissel. From the sides of his head, a pair of white antlers spread to the corners of the cover.

fields.Title: You: "Read the editor's note."
fields.Dialogue Text: Read the editor's note.

fields.Title: You: "[Put the magazine away.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: [Put the magazine away.]

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""What do you expect? It was laying..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "What do you expect? It was laying around the office of the Débardeurs' Union. They're probably *bankrolling* the thing."

fields.Title: La Fumée, Vol. 1 No. 4: "Face it, you really aren't interest..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Face it, you really aren't interested in foreign affairs. You're not even sure where most of these countries are...

fields.Title: La Fumée, Vol. 1 No. 4: "Apparently the material conditions..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Apparently the material conditions of other countries hold no interest for you. Your brand of communism is strictly local. So be it...

fields.Title: La Fumée, Vol. 1 No. 4: "According to this extremely credulo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: According to this extremely credulous account, 'Uncle Sport' (as he's affectionately known to his people) has recently decreed bear wrestling the national sport of the SRV.

fields.Title: La Fumée, Vol. 1 No. 4: "According to the SRV's Ministry of..."
fields.Dialogue Text: According to the SRV's Ministry of Information, the programme has been a tremendous success. Public support stands at 87%, and youth obesity and alcoholism rates are down 12% and 7% respectively.
